adjectives.description: tetched (comparative more tetched, superlative most tetched)

entries.meaning: (chiefly US, colloquial) Touched: mildly deranged, somewhat mentally dysfunctional.
examples: Just because he has trouble with the last verse of the Star Spangled Banner doesn't mean he's tetched. Maybe he has a mental block because you've been hammering him over the skull for three years about it.

entries.meaning: (chiefly US, colloquial) Touched: physically contacted, impacted, or handled.
examples: "They ain't bin tetched or handled by any one but the Kempany's agents."
